# ğŸ‘ ASL Translator â€“ Real-Time American Sign Language Letter Recognition

This project converts American Sign Language (ASL) hand gestures into readable text in real time using 
computer vision and machine learning. It uses a webcam feed, detects hand landmarks, extracts features, and predicts the signed letter on-screen.

---

## ğŸš€ Features
- Real-time hand tracking and landmark detection  
- Recognizes ASL letters Aâ€“Z  
- Machine learning model trained on a custom dataset  
- Works with any webcam  
- Fast inference using a lightweight model  
- Built with Python, OpenCV, and scikit-learn  

---

## ğŸ§° Tech Stack
- Python  
- OpenCV  
- Mediapipe  
- Scikit-Learn  
- NumPy  
- Joblib  

---

## ğŸ“‚ Project Structure

- collect_data.py â€“ record ASL letter images  
- features.py â€“ extract hand landmark features  
- train_model.py â€“ train the ML model  
- realtime_predict.py â€“ **main script** for real-time translation  
- hand_viewer.py â€“ visualize hand landmarks  
- asl_letters_model.joblib â€“ trained model file  
- output.txt â€“ prediction logs  
- X.npy, y.npy and related files â€“ saved dataset and splits  

